=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the brominated aza-heteroaryl ester coupling partner, e.g. methyl bromo-azaheteroaryl carboxylate COC(=O)c1ccc2cncc(Br)c2n1. | Step 2: Prepare the Suzuki partner 4-(1-methyl-1H-pyrazol-4-yl)phenylboronic acid, Cn1ncc(-c2ccc(B(O)O)cc2)c1 (for example from the corresponding bromoaryl pyrazole by Miyaura borylation). | Step 3: Suzuki coupling of COC(=O)c1ccc2cncc(Br)c2n1 with Cn1ncc(-c2ccc(B(O)O)cc2)c1 (Pd catalyst, base) gives the biaryl ester COC(=O)c1ccc2cncc(-c3ccc(-c4cnn(C)c4)cc3)c2n1. | Step 4: Hydrolyze the methyl ester to the acid O=C(O)c1ccc2cncc(-c3ccc(-c4cnn(C)c4)cc3)c2n1. | Step 5: Activate the acid (e.g. SOCl2 to acid chloride, or HATU/EDC) and couple with 4-methoxybenzylamine, COc1ccc(CN)cc1, to furnish the target COc1ccc(CNC(=O)c2ccc3cncc(-c4ccc(-c5cnn(C)c5)cc4)c3n2)cc1.

